good wooden floor cleaner anybody knows an easy way to clean the wooden floor of the kitchen sometimes even if you use mop it still leaves some stains behind i want something easy to wipe that stains out wood floor maintenance most wood floors can be kept clean by first sweeping or vacuuming with a floor nozzle to remove most of the surface dust and dirt then damp mopping with clear water dip a sponge in clear water squeezing it out so that the mop is barely damp almost dry use very little water and rinse your mop thoroughly after each use since excess water can dissolve protective coatings alter the color of the wood and raise the grain to roughen the surface if your floors are not dirty enough to need mopping every week then you should not do it as it will wear the floors faster not to mention waste your time simply sweeping is often all they need if need to restore the shine to your wood floor after you get it clean try damp mopping it with cup vinegar and tablespoons furniture polish in a gallon of warm water vinegar is also useful for removing any soap residue or build up but should not be necessary every week Vacuum cleaner Vinegar Upholstery Dry cleaning Brewery Menstrual cup Soap Car washing techniques Dishwasher Wok Dishwashing Casting Manicure Wood Diving suit Gilding Textile manufacturing Mattress Violin Soldering Kitchen Japanese toilet Fire extinguisher Lighting Drill bit Coffee Hamster Carpet Bong Carburetor Sento Soap bubble Printmaking Wood carving Motorcycle Japanese tea ceremony Home repair Plastic Friction Seismic retrofit Naval mine Phosphoric acid Japanese cuisine Sewage treatment Sulfuric acid Paint Hat Compost Primer (paint) Tattoo Houseplant Vacuum Pottery Fan (implement) Comanche Toilet paper Laundry detergent Deforestation Tobacco Tea Diseases of the honeybee Wind turbine Hemp Hard disk Lacquer Irrigation Dundas Square Cast iron Sodium hypochlorite Fire fighting Chopsticks Jewish cuisine Printed circuit board Cleanliness Laundry Barbecue Ro